As a Senior Software developer specialized in golang 1.22 and interacting with mongodb 7, using the following structs

```go
//base struct
type MyBase struct{
    id int `bson:"_id"`
    name string `bson:"name"`
}

type Specialized struct{
    MyBase
    name2 string `bson:"name"`
}
```
I want to be able to insert into Mongodb the same record twice but with different form, usin polymorphism, like this:
```go
//assume boilerplate
mySpecialized := &Specialized{
    id : 1,
    name: "baseName",
    name2: "mycustomName",
}
coll := client.Database(mConfig.Database).Collection(mConfig.Collection)
/*
{
    "id" : 1, 
    "name": "baseName",
    "name2": "mycustomName",
}
*/
// update id to not collide
_, _ := coll.InsertOne(ctx, mySpecialized.MyBase, ...) 
/*
It should look like this on mongodb
{
    "id" : 110454545,
    "name": "baseName",
    "name2": "mycustomName",
}
*/
// update id to not collide
_, _ := coll.InsertOne(ctx, mySpecialized, ...) 
```

Gimme a func that will cover this scenario, asume the func looks like this:
```go
    func InsertHands(h Specialized) error{
        // missing code
    }

```
